Sorry for all the raspberry language. Lol as a newly recovered codependent, it just makes me so angry when people assume that no one else in the world is working on themselves because they aren’t.

Ways to establish this connection:
Yoga 
Meditation
Journaling or Brain Dump Writing
Somatic Practicing (which is a tool i use in my Human Design coaching)
Jogging 
Dance

Anything that makes you aware of your body and your thoughts all at once. 

‼️You must exist in the present to build the future. ‼️
The answer is not disassociating, its protecting your beliefs from your environment wuthout losing touch with the environment. Love you! 
Be kind to your mental health during your recovery. 

It also protects you from losing empathy for people less adavanced than you

In late February 2020, terrified but optimistic, I announced on a family FaceTime that my abuser had been arrested. The first response from my ___ was that I needed to understand that “that’s somebody’s son.” A woman who’s abusive marriage had colored much of my childhood. 

That was the first moment that I knew I’d be completely on my own in my fight for Justice. And the moment I realized that many victims survive by submitting to the same social laws that abandoned them. 

Isolated socially by a community more angry at me for speaking up than the abuser for abusing and a worldwide pandemic… I roamed the city at night filming what it felt like to be “left behind”. (The clip above is from this collection)

Many of you would suppose this arouses sadness but every kid that’s ever been bullied knows that there’s peace in solitude. When there’s no one to call… no one to listen to… no one to lift… what you find is your own voice. A familiarity with one’s self that goes uninterrupted by the influence of others. 

Society left me behind and what I gained was the space and opportunity to… save myself

I know I should be generating new content none stop to promote the book now that it’s out but the reality is it was such an emotionally draining work to write, curate, and promote that the moment it dropped I couldn’t really bring myself to interact with it. 

The exhaustion hit. 
The realization that I’m openly discussing wounds that are immoral to have (acknowledging that your mother’s actions or inactions negatively impacted you) hit.

And I just needed space from it for a few weeks. But thank you for all the love and support of this book. I hope my written words feel as fruitful as my spoken words.

That said, I will get caught up on DM’s. Thank you for the love. I haven’t quite been able to bring myself to interact with those either yet. But I’m coming back to life 😅

ALSO to everyone asking if I will ever offer a physical version…. I don’t know. I didn’t expect the book & the content around it to be so popular. 😭 I thought like 12 people MIGHT be interested in buying it. But now that I see… maybe it is time to curate more essays & enlist an editor that can prep the work for print. 

Again, thank you. ❤️

Nah actually I have 10 more cents on the topic 😭 first feminist rant of the year let’s go! 😂

Are we talking about the same God?!! The number one best selling author of all time?!! The one with the number cult following world wide?!! The name that when invoked you forgive all manner of evil people regardless of whether they’ve actually changed because it’s good publicity any time someone “turns to God”?!! 

That’s your proof that popularity and being likable means nothing?!!!

Sorry guys, as a someone who built an audience of nearly 400k across all platforms just sharing my opinion, over opinionated but still voted president and chair of every organization I joined in school & professionally, I didn’t realize that pretending to be who you are not was the only way to be popular or likable. 😃 I understand the confusion now.

😂 But in all seriousness, do you get my point? In most scenarios the only person that believes you can’t be yourself and likable/popular… is you. 
‼️Being popular or likable doesnt mean every person you meet likes you or that every person that likes you is your friend. ‼️ 

Intimacy is always kind but kindness is not always intimate… you can be kind, engaged, and friendly without sacrificing yourself.
